##The journey of Italian businessman: Why is it so hard for overseas individuals to donate?

On the last day of January, Ni Zhongbo, a Wenzhou businessman living in Venice, saw a message in his circle of Friends: Alibaba has opened a green channel for free global transportation of epidemic prevention materials, but the hotline does not accept individual donations.

After the outbreak of new crown pneumonia, many overseas procurement resources have been connected with the joint ventures of provincial and municipal governments in China, but there are few channels for individual donations. "want to donate, but do not know how" has become a lot of concern about the epidemic of overseas individual donors face a common problem. This atmosphere of anxiety also permeates the Overseas Wenzhou People's circle.

Ni called several other business-friendly friends in Europe, and the decision was quickly made: to set up a trans-european public logistics group to create a "Green Channel" for individual donors, directional help Wenshang will epidemic prevention materials docking to Wenzhou.

Wenzhou, 900 km from Wuhan, is one of the hardest hit areas by the new outbreak of pneumonia. As of February 14,496 new cases of pneumonia had been confirmed in Wenzhou, the largest number of confirmed cases in any single city outside prefecture of the People's Republic of China. There are 180,000 Wenzhou merchants in Wuhan for business, returning home with many imported cases during the Spring Festival. But at the same time, there are 700,000 Wenzhou people living abroad. They make use of the advantages of doing business and the network of fellow villagers all over the world to purchase, transport and connect with each other in different countries, becoming the strongest force of "sweeping goods" in the overseas aid epidemic force.

But even for the "magical power" of Wen merchants, the donation of materials back home, is also a difficult road.

####"No supplies, no logistics. "

Ni has been in Italy for 26 years. He has been in the garment business for many years and is currently the executive director of the Federation of Overseas Chinese and Industry and Commerce in Veneto.

On January 23, the news that Zhejiang had launched a "first-level response to major public health emergencies" sent Wenzhou residents in Europe into a tizzy. Ni and his friends quickly bought 5,000 masks and sent them back to their hometown in Wenzhou by DHL International Express.

Ni Zhongbo realized that the domestic situation is "no shortage of goods and money, " so priority should be donated, especially the first-line needs of medical masks, protective clothing and thermometers. "Overseas Wenzhounese not only have high enthusiasm for donation, but also have unique advantages, " Ni told interface news.

Wenzhou people from business, familiar with procurement channels, purchase can be directly contact manufacturers. Compared with retail, can save about 40-50% of the price difference. A protective suit, for example, retails for about $10, while the wholesale price is only $6.

At the same time, due to the opening of restaurants, supermarkets, Wenzhou businessmen all over the small towns abroad. Unlike big cities, where pharmacies are sold out by the Chinese, small Chinese tend to be small, easy to shop for, and less likely to raise prices or run out of stock.

How can I donate my stuff back to my country? For individual donors, this is not automatic. The logistics problem is the first to hit.

ALIBABA's Greenway is the main source of free shipping for overseas donors, but it focuses on large, export-qualified donations. It specifically states that "precious capacity should be reserved for more life-saving supplies" and therefore "individual donations will not be accepted for transportation" .

If take international express business such as DHL  , EMS to carry on mail, need to pay expensive logistics fees. A case of masks worth 1,000 euros can cost as much as 490 euros, which is more than ordinary people can afford.

Another option is to "put a man to sleep" -- as someone you know would pack a suitcase on a flight to Florida -- but that was no longer possible after Italy announced on January 30th that it would suspend all flights from China.

Ni Zhongbo and friends a total, set the Public Welfare Group Strategy: "Do not donate materials, donate logistics. ".

They found warm business friends around them, raised 250,000 yuan of start-up capital, all used to pay for DHL's international express costs. If the individual donors intend to donate to Wenzhou, the Public Welfare Group will bear the freight and docking logistics.

The process is: after the individual buys the goods, the group will place an order at DHL and pick up the goods directly at the door. The door-to-door approach eliminates the need to collect goods to the warehouse. The panel determined that the weight of each box of materials should be limited to between 20 and 100 kilograms, so that only small donations by individuals would be accepted and no large donations by institutions would be accepted.

####"4 levels. " "12 files. "

But waiving shipping costs is only the first hurdle.

Bao Shanshan is Ni Zhongbo's first contact with the Friends of Wen Shang, is also one of the sponsors of the Public Welfare Group. She works in cross-border e-commerce and has spent years commuting between Italy and China. Her familiarity with international logistics enabled her to quickly figure out the "go-through" steps needed for cross-border donations.

The first supplies Bao sent home were 5,400 masks donated to Wenzhou No. 6 People's Hospital. She has a friend who works as a nurse at the hospital, and "the nurses are crying, " as if there weren't enough masks, so they only get one a day, but in theory they need to change every four hours.

"It took eight days for the masks to arrive, at least four checkpoints to be cleared and at least 12 documents to be prepared by the donors, " she told screen news, "after we walked through it, we realized how difficult it is for individuals overseas to make donations. "

A package from Italy to the designated Wenzhou Hospital, the need to pass through four checkpoints include: Italian customs, Chinese Customs, Wenzhou Health Commission, the hospital.

In Italy, goods purchased in the name of an individual are generally not invoiced, and additional invoices and customs export declarations are required if they are to be exported through customs.

After arriving at Chinese customs, customs clearance is required. Customs clearance is required to prove that the goods are intended for donation, otherwise they will be subject to customs duties. This needs to be prepared in advance by the Wenzhou Health Commission sealed letter of intent to donate, customs declaration letter, etc. .

Materials passed the customs to reach Wenzhou Health Committee, but also need to register storage. Goods entering in the name of an individual are different from those entering in the name of a group and require additional registration. And then it was sent to the hospital.

The outbreak coincided with the Chinese New Year, and DHL's China office was on vacation, Ms. Bao recalled. She knows DHL's China executives, who help coordinate the shift staff and work overtime to help with customs clearance. They had previously made contact with the Wenzhou Health Commission, emergency "green light. ". In order to ensure that the materials can reach the designated hospital, DHL executives personally went to Wenzhou Health Commission, in the warehouse after registration, overnight supplies to the hospital.

"Most individual donors don't have the channels to coordinate these checkpoints, and the preparation of the 12 documents is a big headache, " she said.

####Self-help of Wenzhou people

The group was officially launched on February 2. Ni Zhongbo and Bao Shanshan posted the news on their friends'circle, and it quickly spread among the Wenzhou community overseas.

The team began a round-the-clock operation: A group of ten people, half in the country and half in Europe. The morning docking Wenzhou Health Committee, the afternoon docking European donors and DHL.

There are a lot of details that need to be worked out, she says. For example, DHL has different rules for the delivery process in European countries. In Germany, exports of more than $1,000 are subject to domestic declaration; in Italy they are not. In Germany, it's by mail. In Greece, it's by phone.

Bao Shanshan observed that Wen merchants showed unprecedented solidarity in the face of the epidemic. "In fact, there is more or less competition and less cooperation among the Wen merchants abroad. But this situation comes out, the various logistics transfer companies are united, you out of a few cars, I also out of a few cars. Wondering how I could help instead of just looking."

According to Huang Xinya, another founder of the group, Wenzhou Society has always had a tradition of self-help. This outbreak, many people's most simple idea is, how can I buy more masks, donated to my home village.

"Many individual donors will have doubts, " Bao explained, adding that most Wenzhou people still want to donate to their hometown. For example, the county-level city of Wenzhou, Ruian is now a bad epidemic, Ruian people hope to be targeted donations to the Hospital Ryan. They will worry, things will not be in the customs to donate, or directly requisitioned by Wuhan? If you go to Wenzhou, can you go to a designated hospital? The Pro Bono group is temporary. Can I trust you?

As of Feb. 7, they had helped ship 573 boxes of supplies back to Wenzhou, including 200,000 masks, 100,000 protective clothing, 155 gloves and 680 warming guns, according to Ni.

What impressed Ni Zhongbo was an old lady from the Netherlands. Through acquaintances, she found a charity group and hoped to donate half of her 5,000 masks to Hangzhou and half to Wenzhou. Ni Zhongbo very want to help, but the public welfare group currently only opened the channel to Wenzhou, can not be sent to Hangzhou.

Ni hopes to extend the experience of the group to more cities. They are also consulting with Chinese communities in the United States, Australia and Africa. For individual donors who want to ship goods to China in a similar way, Ni suggested that the relevant customs documents be prepared in advance.
